From b35788244a916f792a28105a1f974824a60e22e5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Parsa Ghasemi <paarseus@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 14:50:25 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Raytrace-clear stale LETHAL cells (PR3)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Mirror nav2_costmap_2d::ObstacleLayer::raytraceFreespace. For each
bufferSegmentation call, capture the sensor origin + all finite,
in-range cloud points (in global_frame_) into a ClearingObservation.
In SemanticSegmentationLayer::updateBounds, before the existing
tile-iteration marking loop, walk Bresenham rays from the sensor origin
to each captured point and write FREE_SPACE along the way.

This restores the architectural intent already documented in the source
(segmentation_buffer.hpp:664-667 doxygen for raytrace_min_range /
raytrace_max_range — copy-pasted from nav2 ObservationBuffer but never
implemented). It also closes the gap where the plugin was write-only
into costmap_, leaving cells stuck LETHAL until rolling-window scroll
or the global clear-costmap service.

New per-source params (all default off / sensible):
  clearing            : enable per-frame clearing capture (default false)
  raytrace_max_range  : meters, default 8.0
  raytrace_min_range  : meters, default 0.0

Verified 2026-04-29 on a Jetson Orin running ZED X front + HSV
perception pipeline:
  - cells held 42 LETHAL while observations were live
  - cells dropped 42 -> 0 within one cycle (~200ms) after suppressing
    new observations
  - prior to this patch, cells stayed frozen at their last value
    indefinitely (was 7 LETHAL frozen for 8.5s+ in a baseline test)
---
